examples.en: The country is defended with a strong navy.
She defended her beliefs with great vigor.
Virginia had defended her land victoriously.
She defended her position exceptionally well.
He has always loyally defended the president.
The Celts defended their lands against the Romans.
He defended his client's civil rights trenchantly.
The Georgian forces defended the capital but were finally obliged to concede.
Mr Davis defended the government's record on unemployment (=what they have done about unemployment).
